      "uuid": "5e4534f5-fd0d-4598-bfe6-a9857f7e6dc8",
      "source": "NVD",
      "vulnId": "CVE-2025-58457",
      "description": "Improper permission check in ZooKeeper AdminServer lets authorized clients to run snapshot and restore command with insufficient permissions.\n\nThis issue affects Apache ZooKeeper: from 3.9.0 before 3.9.4.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to version 3.9.4, which fixes the issue.\n\nThe issue can be mitigated by disabling both commands (via admin.snapshot.enabled and admin.restore.enabled), disabling the whole AdminServer interface (via admin.enableServer), or ensuring that the root ACL does not provide open permissions. (Note that ZooKeeper ACLs are not recursive, so this does not impact operations on child nodes besides notifications from recursive watches.)",
      "cvssV3BaseScore": 4.3,
      "severity": "MEDIUM",
      "severityRank": 2,
